Greek School Merger Plan Sparks Protests, Strikes, Ta Nea Says

-- B y   M a r i a   P e t r a k i s
-- 
2011-03-15T07:05:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/greek-school-merger-plan-sparks-protests-strikes-ta-nea-says.html
Greek government plans to merge
1,933 schools around the country have prompted protests from
parents, teachers and students, Ta Nea newspaper reported,
without saying how it got the information.   Students are boycotting lessons and taking over school
buildings in protest, the Athens-based newspaper said. Teacher
unions plan a walkout for this week and have proposed a 24-hour
strike for March 30, the newspaper said.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Maria Petrakis at 
 mpetrakis@bloomberg.net  